node.text:
Most of my life I've distanced myself from my Eastern European immigrant background, and the rigidity, pressure, expectations and strict upbringing that came with it. 

Today, I embrace a coming-of-age filled with both struggle and the conquest of enormous social, financial, and emotional challenges. 

I feel so fortunate to work for Sebastian Siemiatkowski, who shares a similar coming-of-age story as the son of Polish immigrants to Sweden. What he has built against all odds is remarkable, and he does it with discipline, focus, and empathy. 

The change he is pioneering now by giving back and challenging the entire tech industry to do so with a 1% pledge to sustainability initiatives emanating from every single fundraising round Klarna does is so inspiring. 

I've never known my parents to be prouder of me because I'm working for Klarna and especially for Sebastian!

node.title: Working at Klarna has true meaning for me.

“Because if they win, we all win.”

 I’m so proud to be on the board of the Norrsken Foundation, founded by Niklas Adalberth, co-founder of Klarna.

 We have just launched the “Y Combinator of Impact” with the aim of incubating, seeding and growing the world’s first sustainability unicorn.

 To solve some of our planet's greatest challenges, such as poverty, food waste, mental health, cancer, pollution or pandemics, we need to think, build, invest and lead in a radically different manner than we have until now.

 Working at the heart of transforming tech and leadership is my passion and the red thread of my career. I’m honored to work with the Norrsken team, proud to serve with my fellow board members and especially excited to welcome my dear friend Avid Larizadeh-Duggan OBE to the board!

 2021 will be the year to drive the creation of true impact unicorns!

 If you’re a startup please Apply to the Norrsken Impact Accelerator 2021. Link in Bio. @niklasadalberth @engellaunilsson @carlmanneh @avidl @markrpcv @norrskenfoundation 🔥

“The essence of the climate challenge we face is that our children and children’s children because of the impacts of climate change and the Arctic are going to see the basic outlines of human society that they inherited from us contracting, creating ‘haves’ and ‘have nots’, some who live well and some who live awfully.

As these ice sheets melt, sea level rises and the water has to go somewhere. Six feet sea level rise wipes out Miami and Washington, D.C.” – Mark Brzezinski.

Proud of my husband Mark who spoke on Morning Joe yesterday on the global implications of the melting Antarctic ice sheet and the wild fires in the U.S. West. “Things will not get cooler”, as our American leadership said yesterday. We need to galvanize global leadership across business, society, and politics across generations to drive solutions. @morningjoe @mikabrzezinski @joescarborough @msnbc #arctic #climatechange

node.text: “We have fragmented our alliances, we have turned against our friend, and we have coddled our enemies.”- Ambassador Mark Brzezinski, my husband killing it on Morning Joe today discussing the geopolitics of this critical moment and the strategic opportunities of the current Belarus crisis. Mark appeared alongside my brother-in-law Joe and Richard Haas, President of the Council on Foreign Relations and longtime family friend. Mark you were amazing! @mikabrzezinski @morningjoe @joescarborough @mark.brzezinski

node.text: In less than 2 hours, my husband Mark will address the Polish-American community across the nation on behalf of VP Joe Biden and his vision for a better, stronger, more just America. Vice President Biden once gave me transformative advice when I was a 26-yr-old new mother heading abroad to serve alongside Mark as an Ambassadorial couple. I’ve carried this advice with me since and passed it on to our daughter. Take a listen! Also don’t forget to tune in to Mark’s Biden call at 4pm ET. I’m so proud of Mark and the amazing legacy he has given our family and the Polish-American diaspora as a whole not just because of his professional accomplishments but because of his character. The registration zoom link is in my bio! @joebiden

I’m so excited to share that Klarna has reached a record 20 Million users today!

I joined Klarna last October and was plunged into the hyper-growth journey of a lifetime! Klarna grew by nearly 1 Million users a month since then, and doubled its U.S. customer base since June 2020.

Today, the Klarna app maintains 4 million monthly active U.S. users and daily downloads surpass our closest competitor by 20%. We’ve launched with inspiring brands such as Jessica Alba’s The Honest Company, Yoox Net-a-Porter, Moncler, Petco, Prabal Gurung, DVF, Charlotte Tilbury, Bed Bath & Beyond and many more.

Klarna is quietly pioneering innovation in luxury, sustainability, financial literacy, in-store activation and driving the fintech revolution. 

I’m so grateful for my Klarna journey and for the amazing colleagues I learn from and am inspired by every day. This role and team has been a daily source of energy, growth, comaraderie and motivation for me.

Congratulations Klarna! The Sky is truly the Limit @klarna.usa @klarna 🔥

node.text:
“Leaders need to express vulnerability. It’s the No. 1 leadership trait to be able to articulate to your organization and beyond who you are as a human being and how you share that to make people feel that they, too, are going through things and you’re there with them- that becomes motivating.” -Mindy Grossman, CEO of WW International Inc. 
 
I’m thrilled to interview Mindy, one of the most pioneering CEO’s of my generation, on our Clubhouse show ‘Your Move’ in a few weeks! Grossman leads with the principle that position, titles and pedigree don’t define power. Impact defines power.
 
She has grown an impact-driven community and wellness movement rooted in the values of accessibility, honesty, openness and compassion. We need more leaders doing things differently.

 Stay tuned for what will be a beautiful and raw conversation!

Follow Klarna's 'Your Move' Club on Clubhouse for more real and thought provoking  conversations this Fall! @mindygrossman @ww @klarna.usa @klarna @clubhouse

node.text:
I’ve been incredibly fortunate to work with and know some of our time’s greatest founders and entrepreneurs.

Founders are fearless. They are shameless and dogged in their pursuit of taking on flawed, old establishment thinking across business, society and culture. Founders have taught me to reject fear and shame.

We need to leverage the founder mentality to address what I believe will be the next great pandemic: burnout and mental health.

I share stories with creative people, especially women and youth, every day. A vast majority are silently suffering or struggling with the weight of this moment. The pandemic has crudely torn the lid off of whatever was not working in our lives and put enormous pressure on all families.

Leaning in to the tech and entrepreneurial community now brings me so much optimism and hope. I’m thrilled to see initiatives like this one from Harry’s and its fantastic founders, Jeff Raider and Andy Katz-Mayfield, called Open Minds investing 5 million USD for the next big idea in mental health! Link in Bio.

I will be interviewing Jeff and Andy on Klarna’s Clubhouse show in September about why they’re investing in mental health. I’m so excited for this catalytic conversation! 

Stay tuned for an amazing slate of speakers we have lined up for Clubhouse this Fall!

“The ocean does not apologize for its depth or crashing waves, and the mountains do not seek forgiveness for the space they take and so, neither shall I.”- Becca Lee. 

Like for many women, this has been the hardest year of my life. I’ve tripped, fallen, gotten drained of energy and risen time and again. The roots of trees get stronger in floods, Mountains harden to thunder and storms.

I’m grateful for everything life has thrown at me. I am awakened and learning every day. I’m understanding my emotions and being gentle with them. I’m making space in my life. I’m powerful and true. 

Everything I learn, I will use to help, advance, support other women and mothers.

“The most important relationship in life is the one you have with yourself.

When it comes down to it, the only thing consistent in your life is you. People come and go, life has ups and downs, but anything can be accomplished and overcome if you appreciate and invest in your relationship with yourself”.- Diane Von Furstenberg. @therealdvf @dvf ❤️

Diane has taught me that when you doubt your power, you give power to your doubt.

Our beautiful conversation (which included her granddaughter Antonia!) reminded me and so many women listening of our true power. I have so much gratitude to Diane for joining me on our Klarna Clubhouse show “Your Move” and for always joining me when I ask for her wisdom and engagement around issues supporting women.

I’m also so grateful to Klarna for believing in women’s empowerment and for empowering me to build initiatives like our Clubhouse show to drive thought leadership and inspiration beyond the confines of everyday business. Only truly transformative companies recognize the power of conversation, culture and impact. 

Thank you for the wings🧚🏼‍♂️ @klarna @klarna.usa @clubhouse

“Chinatown really signifies what New York City means to me.” – Prabal Gurung. 

I’m so proud of the impactful, imaginative way Klarna works with our partners. I love this video we made with my friend Prabal in celebration of Asian-American Pride Month. It focuses on the majestic diversity of New York City as the driver of its success. We also shined a light on the innovative small businesses in the Asian – American community. As the child of immigrants myself, Prabal’s story and Klarna’s story resonate deeply.

 I’m so excited to discuss the immigrant “insider outsider” narrative, the entrepreneurial “hero’s journey” and much more with Prabal and Cuban-American serial founder Alexandra Wilkis Wilson today in a company-wide event I’m delighted to be moderating! @awilkiswilson @prabalgurung @troublewithprabal @klarna.usa @klarna.usa

 Welcome to the Klarna family DVF!
